Through their mastery of armed combat, warriors are able to swing their
weapons in wide arcs, striking multiple opponents simultaneously.  Such
whirlwind attacks can only be attempted periodically, as they can throw
the warrior off-balance and are draining on even the most veteran warriors.


Technical description: Whirlwind attempts to strike all non-grouped entities
within the room.  A skill-success check is applied for attempting the maneuver,
and then a separate hit-check is applied for each and every non-grouped entity.
